<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057112-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 5 and A = 10 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>28.4</li><li>28.8</li><li>80.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({10}\right)}}}=\frac{{5}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{5}}{{\tan{{\left({10}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{28.356409098089}\approx{28.4}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={5}^{{2}}+{28.356409098089}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={25}+{804.08593693816}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={829.08593693816}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{829.08593693816}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{28.793852415718}\approx{28.8}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{10}^{\circ}\approx{80}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>